    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="513"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                <head>No. 58.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rives</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Garland</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-10-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 17, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your letter of the 11th instant, in
                    relation to the postponement of the sale of the British schooners condemned for
                    taking seals in Behring Sea in 1887, I have the honor to inclose herewith a copy
                    of a note received yesterday from the British minister, bearing <pb facs="0858"
                        n="1816" xml:id="pg_1816"/> date the 12th instant, on the same subject; and
                    shall be glad to receive an expression of your views on the arrangement proposed
                    by the British Government in regard to the disposition of the vessels.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. L. Rives.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
